songs.title: Where Did the Sun Go?
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I've been feeling some weight on my shoulders
I'm carrying a shitload of baggage
And you carried us through, you're a soldier
But now you're making claims for the damage

[Pre-Chorus 1]
Together forever
Is something they're selling us
The pressure will test ya
So here's the best of luck to you and me

[Chorus]
Heading off to the unknown
It goes, our daylight fades
It goes
Someone tell me where did the sun go?
Someone tell me where did the sun go?
Someone tell me where did the sun go?

[Verse 2]
Let me tell you how it exactly is
So hard, hard to find happiness
So many fakes, yeah, actors, actresses
Don't let them bite you, spot the draculas
One day everything's immaculate
The next day it's Montague-Capulet
Another day I'm gonna feel miraculous
Looking for the sun, man, I'm an activist

Tell me, tell me, where did the sun go?

[Pre-Chorus 2]
Together forever
Is something they're selling us
The pressure, it gets to
Every one of us eventually

[Chorus]

[Verse 3]
Late at the party, taking it too far
Rabbiting away man, zippidy doo-da
If they asking, last man standing
Hustling, gambling, throwing my hand in
I probably shouldn't mess up my heartbeat
It all starts sweet, then it gets dark quick
Another quick romance? No chance
Always gonna be another girl on the market

[Chorus/Outro]
(Someone tell me where did the sun, someone tell me where did the sun)
(Someone tell me where did the sun, someone tell me where did the sun go?)
Someone tell me where did the sun go?
Someone tell me where did the sun go?
Someone tell me where did the sun go?
Someone tell me where did the sun?
